<div type="translation" source="bib:Gillet2017_01">

<p>Hail! Prosperity! <supplied reason="subaudible">This is</supplied> the year opposite to the year, opposite to the 4th year <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> of king Māṟañcaṭaiyaṉ. We, the Sabhā of Tuṟaiyūrkkuṭi in <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> carāvurnāṭu, <supplied reason="subaudible">for*</supplied> Mahādeva of Tirukkuraṅkāṭutuṟai in Tiraimūrnāṭu <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> as long as the moon and the sun endure, everyday, will have to supply <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>aṭṭakkaṭava</foreign></supplied> one <foreign>uri </foreign>of oil. This is under the protection of the Paṉmāheśvaras.</p></div>

